====Verb====
{{en-verb2|'''help'''|'''[[helps]]'''|'''[[helped]]''' ''or'' (''archaic'') '''[[holp]]'''|'''[[helped]]''' ''or'' (''archaic'') '''[[holpen]]'''|'''[[helping]]'''}}

# {{transitive}} To provide [[assistance]] to (someone or something).
#:* He '''helped''' his grandfather cook breakfast.
#:* If you’re hungry, '''help''' yourself to some of the appetizers.
# {{transitive}} To contribute in some way to.
#:* The white paint on the walls '''helps''' make the room look brighter.
# {{intransitive}} To provide assistance.
#:* She was struggling with the groceries, so I offered to '''help'''.
# {{transitive}} To [[avoid]]; to [[prevent]]; to [[refrain]] from; to [[restrain]] (oneself).  Usually used in the negative with ''[[can]]''.
#:* We couldn't '''help''' noticing that you were late.
#:* She’s trying not to smile, but she can't '''help''' herself.
#:* Try to '''help''' from doing that again.
#:* No one will make a goal today if I can '''help''' it.
# {{context|Chinese English}} To provide a [[favor]].
#:* ''Can you '''help''' me to take a picture?''
#:*: Could you take a picture for me?

